        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 17 at 8:05PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 805 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Statesville, moving northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Statesville, Cooleemee, Harmony, Turnersburg, Sheffield, Cool
Springs, Woodleaf, and Olin.
</description>
        <instruction>Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
